usdIsisMIB.name: usdIsisMIB

revisions.description: Added support for simple password protection.
Initial version of this MIB module, based on draft-ietf-isis-wg-mib.

usdIsisMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdIsisMIB.description: The intermediate system to intermediate system (IS-IS) routing protocol MIB for Unisphere Networks routing switch products. This MIB provides objects for management of the IS-IS Routing protocol, as described in ISO 10589, when it is used to construct routing tables for IP networks, as described in RFC 1195.

OSINSAddress.name: OSINSAddress
OSINSAddress.description: OSI Network Service Address, e.g. NSAP, Network Entity Title

OperState.name: OperState
OperState.description: Type used in enabling and disabling a row.

AuthTime.name: AuthTime
AuthTime.description: Then number of seconds since Jan. 1 1970.

LSPBuffSize.name: LSPBuffSize
LSPBuffSize.description: Integer sub range for LSP size.

SupportedProtocol.name: SupportedProtocol
SupportedProtocol.description: Types of network protocol supported by Integrated ISIS. The values for ISO8473 and IP are those registered for these protocols in ISO TR9577.

UsdDefaultMetric.name: UsdDefaultMetric
UsdDefaultMetric.description: Integer sub-range for default metric for single hop. The value is truncated to 63 when the usdIsisSysL1MetricStyle or usdIsisSysL2MetricStyle is set to usdIsisMetricStyleNarrow

OtherMetric.name: OtherMetric
OtherMetric.description: Integer sub-range for metrics other than the default metric for single hop.

usdIsisSysTable.name: usdIsisSysTable
usdIsisSysTable.description: The set of instances of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.

usdIsisSysEntry.name: usdIsisSysEntry
usdIsisSysEntry.description: Each row defines information specific to a single instance of the protocol existing on the system.

usdIsisSysInstance.name: usdIsisSysInstance
usdIsisSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisSysVersion.name: usdIsisSysVersion
usdIsisSysVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol to which this instance conforms. This value must be set by the implementation when the row is valid.

usdIsisSysType.name: usdIsisSysType
usdIsisSysType.description: The type of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

usdIsisSysID.name: usdIsisSysID
usdIsisSysID.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the instance's area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles valid for this instance. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may assign values and not permit write MAX-ACCESS, others may require the value to be set manually.

usdIsisSysMaxPathSplits.name: usdIsisSysMaxPathSplits
usdIsisSysMaxPathSplits.description: Maximum number of paths with equal routing metric value which it is permitted to split between. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

usdIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.name: usdIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt
usdIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, between generated LSPs by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

usdIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize.name: usdIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize
usdIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of Level 1 LSPs and SNPs originated by this instance. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

usdIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses.name: usdIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses
usdIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses.description: The maximum number of area addresses to be permitted for the area in which this instance exists. Note that all Intermediate Systems in the same area must have the same value configured for this attribute if correct operation is to be assumed. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

usdIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt.name: usdIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt
usdIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of L1 LSPs with the same LSPID by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

usdIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt.name: usdIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt
usdIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of L2 LSPs with the same LSPID by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

usdIsisSysPollESHelloRate.name: usdIsisSysPollESHelloRate
usdIsisSysPollESHelloRate.description: The value, in seconds, to be used for the suggested ES configuration timer in ISH PDUs when soliciting the ES configuration.

usdIsisSysWaitTime.name: usdIsisSysWaitTime
usdIsisSysWaitTime.description: Number of seconds to delay in waiting state before entering on state. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

usdIsisSysOperState.name: usdIsisSysOperState
usdIsisSysOperState.description: The operational state of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. Setting this object to the value on when its current value is off enables operation of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol.

usdIsisSysL1State.name: usdIsisSysL1State
usdIsisSysL1State.description: The state of the Level 1 database.

usdIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads.name: usdIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads
usdIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads.description: Number of times the LSP L1 database has become overloaded.

usdIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas.name: usdIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas
usdIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas.description: Number of times a manual address has been dropped from the area.

usdIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.name: usdIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums
usdIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.description: Number of times the IS has attempted to exceed the maximum sequence number.

usdIsisSysSeqNumSkips.name: usdIsisSysSeqNumSkips
usdIsisSysSeqNumSkips.description: Number of times a sequence number skip has occurred.

usdIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.name: usdIsisSysOwnLSPPurges
usdIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.description: Number of times a zero-aged copy of the system's own LSP is received from some other node.

usdIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.name: usdIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches
usdIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length to that of the receiving system.

usdIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches.name: usdIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches
usdIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for MaximumAreaAddresses from that of the receiving system.

usdIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.name: usdIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize
usdIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of Level 2 LSPs and SNPs originated by this system. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

usdIsisSysL2State.name: usdIsisSysL2State
usdIsisSysL2State.description: The state of the Level 2 database.

usdIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads.name: usdIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads
usdIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads.description: Number of times the Level 2 LSP database has become overloaded.

usdIsisSysAuthFails.name: usdIsisSysAuthFails
usdIsisSysAuthFails.description: The number of authentication failures recognized by this instance of the protocol.

usdIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors.name: usdIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors
usdIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors.description: If true, allow the router to ignore IS-IS link state packets (LSPs) that are received with internal checksum errors rather than purging the LSPs.

usdIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.name: usdIsisSysMaxAreaCheck
usdIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.description: When on, enables checking of maximum area addresses per IS version of ISO10589.

usdIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration.name: usdIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration
usdIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration.description: Specifies the length in time of seconds to set the overload bit from startup. This object must be set together with usdIsisSysSetOverloadBit, otherwise the agent will return an error.

usdIsisSysMaxLspLifetime.name: usdIsisSysMaxLspLifetime
usdIsisSysMaxLspLifetime.description: Specifies the maximum time (in seconds) a LSP will remain in the box without being refreshed before being considered invalid.

usdIsisSysL1SpfInterval.name: usdIsisSysL1SpfInterval
usdIsisSysL1SpfInterval.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between level 1 SPF calculations.

usdIsisSysL2SpfInterval.name: usdIsisSysL2SpfInterval
usdIsisSysL2SpfInterval.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between level 2 SPF calculations.

usdIsisSysIshHoldTime.name: usdIsisSysIshHoldTime
usdIsisSysIshHoldTime.description: Specify a holdtime advertised in ESH/ISH PDUs.

usdIsisSysIshConfigTimer.name: usdIsisSysIshConfigTimer
usdIsisSysIshConfigTimer.description: Specify the rate of transmission for ESH and ISH packets.

usdIsisSysDistributeDomainWide.name: usdIsisSysDistributeDomainWide
usdIsisSysDistributeDomainWide.description: When on, enables distribution of prefixes throughout a multi-level domain.

usdIsisSysDistance.name: usdIsisSysDistance
usdIsisSysDistance.description: The weight applied to IS-IS routes.

usdIsisSysL1MetricStyle.name: usdIsisSysL1MetricStyle
usdIsisSysL1MetricStyle.description: Specifies the type of IP reachability TLV to advertise in level 1 LSPs.

usdIsisSysL2MetricStyle.name: usdIsisSysL2MetricStyle
usdIsisSysL2MetricStyle.description: Specifies the type of IP reachability TLV to advertise in level 2 LSPs.

usdIsisSysMplsTeLevel.name: usdIsisSysMplsTeLevel
usdIsisSysMplsTeLevel.description: Select flooding of MPLS traffic engineering link information into the specified ISIS level.

usdIsisSysMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.name: usdIsisSysMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex
usdIsisSysMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.description: Configure the stable router interface ID to designate it as TE capable. A value of zero is used to remove any configured router interface ID.

usdIsisManAreaAddrTable.name: usdIsisManAreaAddrTable
usdIsisManAreaAddrTable.description: The set of manual area addresses configured on this Intermediate System.

usdIsisManAreaAddrEntry.name: usdIsisManAreaAddrEntry
usdIsisManAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address manually configured on this system.

usdIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.name: usdIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance
usdIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisManAreaAddr.name: usdIsisManAreaAddr
usdIsisManAreaAddr.description: A manually configured area address for this system. This object follows the index behaviour. Note: an index for the entry {1, {49.0001} active} in this table would be the ordered pair (1, (0x03 0x49 0x00 0x01)), as the length of an octet string is part of the OID.

usdIsisManAreaAddrRowStatus.name: usdIsisManAreaAddrRowStatus
usdIsisManAreaAddrRowStatus.description: The state of the usdIsisManAreaAddrEntry. This object follows the RowStatus behaviour. If an attempt is made to set this object to the value off when the corresponding usdIsisManAreaAddrEntry is the only valid entry for this instance and when the corresponding IS-IS instance has usdIsisSysOperState set to on then the attempt is rejected.

usdIsisSysProtSuppTable.name: usdIsisSysProtSuppTable
usdIsisSysProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of protocols supported by each instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

usdIsisSysProtSuppEntry.name: usdIsisSysProtSuppEntry
usdIsisSysProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by an instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

usdIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.name: usdIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance
usdIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.name: usdIsisSysProtSuppProtocol
usdIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisSysProtSuppRowStatus.name: usdIsisSysProtSuppRowStatus
usdIsisSysProtSuppRowStatus.description: The state of the usdIsisSysProtSuppEntry. This object follows the RowStatus behavior.

usdIsisSummAddrTable.name: usdIsisSummAddrTable
usdIsisSummAddrTable.description: The set of IP summary addresses to use in forming the contents of Level 2 LSPs originated by this level 2 Intermediate System.

usdIsisSummAddrEntry.name: usdIsisSummAddrEntry
usdIsisSummAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address.

usdIsisSummAddrSysInstance.name: usdIsisSummAddrSysInstance
usdIsisSummAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviours.

usdIsisSummAddress.name: usdIsisSummAddress
usdIsisSummAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisSummAddrMask.name: usdIsisSummAddrMask
usdIsisSummAddrMask.description: The mask value for this summary address. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisSummAddrRowStatus.name: usdIsisSummAddrRowStatus
usdIsisSummAddrRowStatus.description: The existence state of this summary address. This object follows the RowStatus behaviour.

usdIsisSummAddrOperState.name: usdIsisSummAddrOperState
usdIsisSummAddrOperState.description: The operational state of this entry. This object follows the operationalState behaviour. When the operational state changes if this would cause the contents of LSPs originated by the system to change then those new LSPs must be generated and sent as soon as is permitted by the ISIS protocol.

usdIsisSummAddrDefaultMetric.name: usdIsisSummAddrDefaultMetric
usdIsisSummAddrDefaultMetric.description: The default metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 1 or 2 LSPs generated by this system. A Metric value of 0 indicates to use the lowest metric value amongst the routes being summarized. When advertising a metric value into a narrow domain (usdIsisSysL1MetricStyle or usdIsisSysL2MetricStyle is set to usdIsisMetricStyleNarrow) the value will be truncated to 63.

usdIsisSummAddrDelayMetric.name: usdIsisSummAddrDelayMetric
usdIsisSummAddrDelayMetric.description: The delay metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisSummAddrExpenseMetric.name: usdIsisSummAddrExpenseMetric
usdIsisSummAddrExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisSummAddrErrorMetric.name: usdIsisSummAddrErrorMetric
usdIsisSummAddrErrorMetric.description: The error metric value to announce this summary address with in Level n LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisSummLevel.name: usdIsisSummLevel
usdIsisSummLevel.description: The level of database at which to annouce this summary.

usdIsisCircTable.name: usdIsisCircTable
usdIsisCircTable.description: The table of circuits used by each instance of Integrated IS-IS on this system.

usdIsisCircEntry.name: usdIsisCircEntry
usdIsisCircEntry.description: An usdIsisCircEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

usdIsisCircSysInstance.name: usdIsisCircSysInstance
usdIsisCircSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisCircIfIndex.name: usdIsisCircIfIndex
usdIsisCircIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds.

usdIsisCircLocalID.name: usdIsisCircLocalID
usdIsisCircLocalID.description: An identification that can be used in protocol packets to identify a circuit. Implementations may devise ways to assure that this value is suitable for the circuit it is used on. LAN packets only have space for 8 bits. Values of usdIsisCircLocalID do not need to be unique. They are only required to differ on LANs where the Intermediate System is the Designated Intermediate System.

usdIsisCircOperState.name: usdIsisCircOperState
usdIsisCircOperState.description: The operational state of the circuit. This object follows the operationalState behaviour.

usdIsisCircRowStatus.name: usdIsisCircRowStatus
usdIsisCircRowStatus.description: The existence state of this circuit. This object follows the RowStatus behaviour.

usdIsisCircType.name: usdIsisCircType
usdIsisCircType.description: The type of the circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour. The type specified must be compatible with the type of the interface defined by the value of usdIsisCircIfIndex.

usdIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.name: usdIsisCircL1DefaultMetric
usdIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic.

usdIsisCircL1DelayMetric.name: usdIsisCircL1DelayMetric
usdIsisCircL1DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.name: usdIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric
usdIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.name: usdIsisCircL1ErrorMetric
usdIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisCircExtDomain.name: usdIsisCircExtDomain
usdIsisCircExtDomain.description: If true, suppress normal transmission of and interpretation of Intra-domain ISIS PDUs on this circuit.

usdIsisCircAdjChanges.name: usdIsisCircAdjChanges
usdIsisCircAdjChanges.description: The number of times an adjacency state change has occurred on this circuit.

usdIsisCircInitFails.name: usdIsisCircInitFails
usdIsisCircInitFails.description: The number of times initialization of this circuit has failed.

usdIsisCircRejAdjs.name: usdIsisCircRejAdjs
usdIsisCircRejAdjs.description: The number of times an adjacency has been rejected on this circuit.

usdIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.name: usdIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs
usdIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs sent on this circuit.

usdIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.name: usdIsisCircInCtrlPDUs
usdIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs received on this circuit.

usdIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.name: usdIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches
usdIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an ID field length different to that for this system has been received.

usdIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.name: usdIsisCircL2DefaultMetric
usdIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic.

usdIsisCircL2DelayMetric.name: usdIsisCircL2DelayMetric
usdIsisCircL2DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.name: usdIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric
usdIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.name: usdIsisCircL2ErrorMetric
usdIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

usdIsisCircManL2Only.name: usdIsisCircManL2Only
usdIsisCircManL2Only.description: When true, indicates that this circuit is to be used only for level 2. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

usdIsisCircL1ISPriority.name: usdIsisCircL1ISPriority
usdIsisCircL1ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN Level 1 Deignated Intermediate System on a broadcast circuit.

usdIsisCircL1CircID.name: usdIsisCircL1CircID
usdIsisCircL1CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of the value (because it is not participating in the Level 1 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

usdIsisCircL1DesIS.name: usdIsisCircL1DesIS
usdIsisCircL1DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

usdIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.name: usdIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges
usdIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

usdIsisCircL2ISPriority.name: usdIsisCircL2ISPriority
usdIsisCircL2ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN level 2 Designated Intermediate System.

usdIsisCircL2CircID.name: usdIsisCircL2CircID
usdIsisCircL2CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of this value (because it is not participating in the Level 2 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

usdIsisCircL2DesIS.name: usdIsisCircL2DesIS
usdIsisCircL2DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason, this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

usdIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.name: usdIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges
usdIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

usdIsisCircMCAddr.name: usdIsisCircMCAddr
usdIsisCircMCAddr.description: Specifies which type of multicast address will be used for sending HELLO PDUs on this circuit.

usdIsisCircPtToPtCircID.name: usdIsisCircPtToPtCircID
usdIsisCircPtToPtCircID.description: The ID of the circuit allocated during initialization. If no value has been negotiated (either because the adjacency is to an End System, or because initialization has not yet successfully completed), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

usdIsisCircL1HelloTimer.name: usdIsisCircL1HelloTimer
usdIsisCircL1HelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in seconds, between Level 1 IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks. It is also used as the period between Hellos on point to point circuits. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

usdIsisCircL2HelloTimer.name: usdIsisCircL2HelloTimer
usdIsisCircL2HelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in seconds, between Level 1 IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

usdIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.name: usdIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier
usdIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS.

usdIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.name: usdIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier
usdIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS

usdIsisCircMinLSPTransInt.name: usdIsisCircMinLSPTransInt
usdIsisCircMinLSPTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in milliseconds, between transmission of LSPs on a circuit. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour. This timer shall be capable of a resolution not coarser than 10 milliseconds.

usdIsisCircMinLSPReTransInt.name: usdIsisCircMinLSPReTransInt
usdIsisCircMinLSPReTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an Level 1 or 2 LSP. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

usdIsisCircL1CSNPInterval.name: usdIsisCircL1CSNPInterval
usdIsisCircL1CSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between transmission of Level 1 CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router. On point-to-point networks the default is to not transmit CSNPs.

usdIsisCircL2CSNPInterval.name: usdIsisCircL2CSNPInterval
usdIsisCircL2CSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between transmission of Level 2 CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router. On point-to-point networks the default is to not transmit CSNPs.

usdIsisCircLSPThrottle.name: usdIsisCircLSPThrottle
usdIsisCircLSPThrottle.description: Minimal interval of time, in milliseconds, between retransmissions of LSPs on a point to point interface.

usdIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled.name: usdIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled
usdIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled.description: Is this port a member of a mesh group, or blocked? Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group.

usdIsisCircMeshGroup.name: usdIsisCircMeshGroup
usdIsisCircMeshGroup.description: Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group. If usdIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled is false, this value is ignored.

usdIsisCircLevel.name: usdIsisCircLevel
usdIsisCircLevel.description: The type of this circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

usdIsisCircState.name: usdIsisCircState
usdIsisCircState.description: The operational state of the circuit.

usdIsisSysHostNameTable.name: usdIsisSysHostNameTable
usdIsisSysHostNameTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of host name to system ID aliases supported by each instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

usdIsisSysHostNameEntry.name: usdIsisSysHostNameEntry
usdIsisSysHostNameEntry.description: Each entry contains one name to system ID alias supported by an instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

usdIsisSysHostNameSysInstance.name: usdIsisSysHostNameSysInstance
usdIsisSysHostNameSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

usdIsisSysHostNameSysId.name: usdIsisSysHostNameSysId
usdIsisSysHostNameSysId.description: The ID for the system which this name will be assigned.

usdIsisSysHostNameAreaAddr.name: usdIsisSysHostNameAreaAddr
usdIsisSysHostNameAreaAddr.description: A configured area address for the system which this name will be assigned. This object follows the index behaviour. Note: an index for the entry {1, {49.0001} active} in this table would be the ordered pair (1, (0x03 0x49 0x00 0x01)), as the length of an Octet string is part of the OID.

usdIsisSysHostNameName.name: usdIsisSysHostNameName
usdIsisSysHostNameName.description: A string to use when displaying system data with this system ID.

usdIsisSysHostNameType.name: usdIsisSysHostNameType
usdIsisSysHostNameType.description: The type of host name entry.

usdIsisSysHostNameRowStatus.name: usdIsisSysHostNameRowStatus
usdIsisSysHostNameRowStatus.description: The status of this host name entry. This object follows the RowStatus behaviour.

usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationTable.name: usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationTable
usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of area authentication keys supported by each instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationEntry.name: usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationEntry
usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationEntry.description: Each entry contains one area authentication key supported by an instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationSysInstance.name: usdIsisSysAreaAuthenticationSysInstance
